Description:
We are a Dutch based software company, with offices in Romania since 2009, and the United Arab Emirates since 2019.

We're excited to announce our expansion into the Philippines and are looking for talented remote professionals to join our international team. Initially, we're starting with 100% remote work opportunities, with plans to establish our office presence in the Clark area.

If you are triggered by the idea of being a part of a new international team while working on industry-leading projects, this is your chance. Join us and enjoy the best of both worlds: the excitement of a new venture and the stability of a company with over three decades of success.

Your role as a Back End Developer

Our R&D / PD team focuses on innovation and improvements of our in-house Low Code Development platform - Codex. Our Low Code Developers use this platform to quickly and functionally create state-of-the-art applications for our customers in a short period. You will ensure that Codex contains all the tools they need to make the best software. You will work with the backend technologies listed in the image below to achieve this. Your activities will include:
• Developing our backend services for our Codex engine;
• Incorporate Domain Driven Design in the Platform;
• Working on containerizing our current architecture;
• Architect and implement the system into a micro-service-based architecture

We keep researching and including technologies like Microservices, Micro Frontend, Event Store, CQRS, and other exciting topics. Our tech stack (not limited to):

Job requirements

We are in search of someone with a focus on solutions and opportunities, not impossibilities. You are eager to learn new things and are adaptable to do so. Furthermore, you have;
• Bachelor in computer science or another related study;
• 10+ years of work experience in .Net development;
• Proven track record with C#, MS SQL, and Azure;
• Preferably hands-on experience with Docker and Kubernetes;
• AI-driven mindset. You embrace the endless opportunities AI can offer us and implement it in your day-to-day work;
• Fluency in English;
• You are curious, eager to learn, and always seeking improvements;
• You reside in the Philippines.

We offer

Being a part of Codeless means that you will always be encouraged to learn new things and explore new options. You will implement the latest technologies and work with like-minded people who all strive for the best software possible. What more can you expect?
• Technical challenging environment (trust us) where you'll get space for your own initiatives, e.g., implement the newest tools and technologies;
• An established organization that has been around for 35 years and that truly cares for its employees;
• An international work environment with colleagues in the Netherlands, Romania, Emirates, and Philippines;
• A great place to work and the opportunity to make a difference and have an impact on all of our customers;
• Competitive and attractive compensation;
• Personal development plan and access to various types of training;
• Paid vacation leave and paid sick leave;
• Health Insurance;
• Remote work.

Recruitment procedure

Has the job piqued your interest? We’d love to see your application!
• Screening our Corporate Recruiter via Teams;
• Online assessment via TestDome;
• Interview with the tech team;
• Final interview with the hiring manager;
• Is it a match? Then we’d love you to join our team!

About Codeless

We modernize legacy software.

Our mission is to help other businesses by building the best software they could wish for.

Codeless, as the creators of Copy To Innovate, is the #1 authority that helps businesses to renew outdated software. With that, we help companies with unique and distinctive processes realize their ambitions by solving complex software challenges, often caused by a constantly changing software landscape. We have been helping businesses realize their ambitions for over 35 years.

We do that with an amazing and diverse team of 100 passionate experts, located in the Netherlands, Romania, the United Arab Emirates, and now also in the Philippines. We are no-nonsense, innovative, and focused on the best results for both our customers and our colleagues.

We offer you a great place to work, where we value our employees. We don’t go for quick wins, but for long-term commitment and excellent collaboration.

Go to https://www.codeless.com/ or https://careers.codeless.com/ for more information.

No recruitment agencies, please.

Job Summary

We are hiring Senior Data Engineer, you will play a critical role in ensuring the quality and stability of Credit Risk Reporting applications. You’ll work closely with cross-functional teams to develop, test, and optimize solutions that meet compliance, regulatory, and business requirements. Your expertise will drive improvements in software quality, data accuracy, and overall system performance in a complex data environment.

Mandatory Skill-set
• Have 5+ years of experience in PowerBI, SQL and data warehousing;
• Have strong knowledge of various test methodologies, including BDD, TDD, and white-box testing, with hands-on experience in tools like Cucumber, Selenium, and Rest Assured;
• Advanced expertise in Oracle databases, including setup, PL/SQL packages, stored procedures, query writing, and query tuning;
• Proficiency in CI/CD with Azure DevOps, setting up new pipelines, and using Ansible for playbooks;
• Foundational knowledge of data warehousing and ETL processes, along with tools such as Azure Data Factory;
• Familiarity with Linux OS and experience working on cloud environments, preferably Azure.

Desired Skill-set
• Familiarity with JMeter, Gatling, Postman, and SoapUI;
• Background in Credit Risk reporting, Banking, or Insurance.

Responsibilities
• Engage actively in all development stages, from Business Analysis to test cycles, to ensure seamless delivery and quality assurance;
• Design, develop, and implement test strategies, plans, and cases, including functional, integration, and system testing;
• Enhance automated testing, improving test coverage, reducing manual effort, and ensuring high-quality code. Increase end-to-end test automation and coverage daily;
• Set up and maintain CI/CD pipelines and related DevOps practices using Azure DevOps, and automate test integration in the development process;
• Conduct data quality checks, data comparisons, and testing of data models, with a focus on PL/SQL, query tuning, and Oracle database environments;
• Improve stability, performance, and reliability of Credit Risk Reporting applications to comply with IT security standards;
• Work with developers, business analysts, and testers to optimize and streamline IT processes and the overall testing approach.

Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest.

When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTE’s website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).

Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews.

