KEY RESPONSIBILITIES AND ACCOUNTABILITIES:

· Installs new/rebuilds existing network equipment and configure hardware, peripherals, services, settings, firewalls, switches, etc. in accordance with standards and project/operational requirements;

· Performs regular security monitoring to identify any possible intrusions;

· Ensures that effective service system is in place and resources are provided and used effectively to support IT service requirements; 4. Provides regular advisory to the IT Head or Chief Technology Officer on the status of various IT networks;

· Performs routine audits of operating network equipment and networks software installed in servers, firewalls, switches and applies updates, patches and configuration changes as necessary;

· Performs quarterly backups of network equipment, including firewall and switch configuration, and submits them for safekeeping to the IT Head or Chief Technology Officer;

· Coordinates with providers for the preventive maintenance of network equipment under contract. Maintains and housekeep all network equipment;

· Assumes responsibility of the day-to-day operation and administration of the network switches, firewalls, monitoring software and other associated network tasks, but not limited to address setting, user setups, and security measures;

· Technical configuration, installation, and monitoring are performed for LAN configurations and other internal and external network requirements;

· Installs and configures new network hardware, as well as any necessary server monitoring software;

· Responsible for putting in place firewall security and documenting how the required network requirements are set;

· Responsible for establishing Networks-level access control for internal and external users that includes VPN and other related access;

· Provides support on problems related to network access. Troubleshoots any reported problems;

· Performs and submits result of network performance tuning and capacity planning of network equipment on semi-annual basis;

· Communicating networking issues to other employees and management, especially in training new users;

· Performs other duties that may be assigned from time to time.

QUALIFICATIONS:

· Bachelor's degree in information technology, Computer or a related field

· At least 3 year’ extensive experience as Network Admin Expertise in Network Administration and Network Infrastructure

· Full knowledge in OSI layer

· Experience with Layer 2 and layer 3 switch

· Skills in Network Security and Troubleshooting

· Experience in DRP

· Experience with Fortigate firewall configurations and management

· Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills

· Able to work effectively on-site

· Experience in System Administration is a plus

· ITIL, CCNA and Fortinet Certificate are a plus

· Provide on call support on weekend and after office hours

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: Php25,000.00 - Php35,000.00 per month

Benefits:
• Additional leave
• Opportunities for promotion
• Paid training
• Promotion to permanent employee

Schedule:
• 8 hour shift

Supplemental Pay:
• 13th month salary

Education:
• Bachelor's (Preferred)

Work Location: In person

