Drake’s top client – an IT company based in Philippines, is currently hiring a Web Developer to be part of their collaborative team in Quezon City!

Responsibilities
• Consults and pairs with Business Systems Analysts for Auxiliary to determine business requirements, functional requirements and input/output requirements;
• Defines web application requirements;
• Analyzes, defines and documents system requirements for data, workflow, logical processes, interfaces with other systems, auditing and reporting requirements and production configuration;
• Develops, codes, tests, and debugs web-based applications and web sites using a back-end database within the framework of the LTO-IT system environment;
• Writes and maintains functional and technical specifications;
• Develops complex software systems including relational databases, business applications using web-based programming languages, web interfaces to multiple information databases, data input handling applications, data transfer among heterogeneous systems and other software systems for all internal and external business processes, applications to implement business rules and other data processing, web to database communications processes and report generation;
• Analyzes code for problem resolution and performance optimizations;
• Provides technical support to Customer Care personnel and responds to error reports, problems or questions;
• Monitors performance of auxiliary applications and provides technical support as required;
• Meets service commitments and assigned deliverables such as but not limited to change request and other enhancements, based on service level agreement;
• Generates reports as requested by clients;
• Participates in production validation and verification activities; and,
• Performs other job-related tasks that may be assigned by his superiors from time to time.

Requirements
• College graduate of Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Math or any IT-related course
• No licensure or certification required.
• Must have at least 3 to 5 years of web development experience
• Knowledgeable in web development, Netcore, ASP.Net, VB.Net, MS SQL, SQL server, PHP, My SQL, Network, HTML, and CSS
• Experience and/or actual knowledge with React JS and Next JS is an advantage.
• Experience with Azure Boards, Azure Repos, Azure Pipelines, and Testplan is an advantage

What's in it for you?
• Career opportunities and advancement
• Work life balance
• Competitive base pay

Additional information

Onsite during probationary period, and hybrid setup once regularized

